MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: (capabilities:\s*\[|createDmChannel|createGroupDmChannel|channelHasCapability.*SILVER_TRANSFER)
ADVISORY: |
  Adding `'SILVER_TRANSFER'` to a channel's `capabilities` list DOES authorize
  silver transfers into that channel server-side. The guard at
  `apps/game-server/src/machines/actions/l3-social.ts:~642` reads:

    if (resolvedChannel && !channelHasCapability(context.channels, resolvedChannel, 'SILVER_TRANSFER'))
      return false;

  So `capabilities` is not just a UI hint — it's the authorization gate for
  SEND_SILVER. If you add the cap to MAIN (needed for `/silver` hint chip
  visibility from MAIN), the server will ACCEPT a SEND_SILVER event with
  `channel: 'MAIN'`. This is an intentional consequence of the unified
  capability model documented in the Phase 2 DM polish spec, but client
  discipline must prevent emitting that shape — the `/silver` picker from
  MAIN always resolves to a DM channelId before firing.

  When adding new channel types or adjusting caps, check for guards that
  consult the cap (grep `channelHasCapability`) and decide whether the new
  channel should genuinely support the action server-side.

  Source: docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-13-pulse-dm-polish-design.md
  (Risks section — "Silver-in-MAIN authorization").
